File: A scientist is at work in the VirPath university laboratory as they try to find an effective treatment against the new coronavirus. JOHANNESBURG - Egypt confirms its first coronavirus case, making this the first in Africa. The Ministry of Health confirmed the case on Friday and says the affected person is a foreigner. READ: Japan cruise ship coronavirus cases climb to 174 The person has been placed in isolation in a hospital and all the necessary measures to contain the virus have been implemented. The World Health Organisation and the ministry are collaborating closely in outbreak investigation and response actions. READ: World scientists meet to fight coronavirus No details regarding the nationality of the infected person have been released. The virus has infected more than 67,000 people globally .